1
00:00:00,064 --> 00:01:00,064
(Watch on www.kisskh.club Support Admin)

2
00:01:19,088 --> 00:01:21,120
Hyun Jin!

3
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:23,666
- You okay?
- Yoon Seong...

4
00:01:25,891 --> 00:01:27,417
Who are you?

5
00:01:27,417 --> 00:01:29,987
What are you doing in her house?

6
00:01:30,575 --> 00:01:32,548
Are you okay?

7
00:01:32,548 --> 00:01:34,465
- I'm so sorry.
- What is this?

8
00:01:34,465 --> 00:01:36,136
What the hell are you doing in her house?

9
00:01:36,136 --> 00:01:37,565
Well...

10
00:01:37,565 --> 00:01:39,817
I was just...

11
00:01:39,817 --> 00:01:41,993
I was going to wait outside,

12
00:01:41,993 --> 00:01:43,537
but the door was open, so...

13
00:01:43,537 --> 00:01:44,579
I mean...

14
00:01:44,579 --> 00:01:46,388
I'm really sorry if I startled you.

15
00:01:46,388 --> 00:01:47,700
Save it.

16
00:01:47,700 --> 00:01:49,101
You can explain at the police station.

17
00:01:49,101 --> 00:01:51,186
Sun Woo Jin.

18
00:01:51,186 --> 00:01:53,679
Is this...

19
00:01:55,148 --> 00:01:57,725
Is this Woo Jin's house?

20
00:01:57,725 --> 00:01:59,818
How do you know

21
00:01:59,818 --> 00:02:02,567
my brother-in-law's name?

22
00:02:02,567 --> 00:02:04,512
Brother-in-law?

23
00:02:05,676 --> 00:02:08,420
[Temporary Helper]

24
00:02:10,181 --> 00:02:12,225
Pick up the phone, please.

25
00:02:12,225 --> 00:02:14,310
The number you're trying to reach is not...

26
00:02:21,554 --> 00:02:23,597
I'm...

27
00:02:24,372 --> 00:02:26,904
Woo Jin's father.

28
00:02:47,934 --> 00:02:49,898
Where's Hyun Jin?

29
00:02:54,685 --> 00:02:55,753
Are you okay?

30
00:02:55,753 --> 00:02:58,373
What happened? You're not hurt, huh?

31
00:02:58,373 --> 00:03:00,189
Yeah, I'm fine.

32
00:03:00,189 --> 00:03:02,801
Then why didn't you answer your phone?
I was worried sick.

33
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:11,380
Who are you?

34
00:03:16,162 --> 00:03:19,006
Are you... Tae Hyung?

35
00:03:30,505 --> 00:03:32,919
Oh, it's obvious.

36
00:03:32,919 --> 00:03:36,218
It's really you, Tae Hyung.

37
00:03:37,710 --> 00:03:38,917
It really is...

38
00:03:38,917 --> 00:03:41,404
Who are you, exactly?

39
00:03:43,725 --> 00:03:46,118
He says he's your father.

40
00:03:58,076 --> 00:04:00,029
I'm sorry.

41
00:04:02,342 --> 00:04:05,519
I came too late.

42
00:04:07,977 --> 00:04:10,143
I'm so sorry, Tae Hyung...

43
00:04:17,435 --> 00:04:18,980
Are you sure you're okay?

44
00:04:18,980 --> 00:04:19,977
I'm fine.

45
00:04:19,977 --> 00:04:21,966
It wasn't a big deal.

46
00:04:21,966 --> 00:04:24,520
I'm really okay, so you should get going.

47
00:04:24,520 --> 00:04:27,355
There was a break-in.
How is that not a big deal?

48
00:04:27,355 --> 00:04:29,634
I spoke to the police earlier.

49
00:04:29,634 --> 00:04:33,259
If anything's missing,
they want you to call right away.

50
00:04:33,259 --> 00:04:35,053
Okay.

51
00:04:35,053 --> 00:04:38,569
Thank you so much today.

52
00:04:38,569 --> 00:04:40,382
No problem.

53
00:04:40,382 --> 00:04:42,563
By the way, where's Woo Joo?

54
00:04:42,563 --> 00:04:47,013
Downstairs. I'll bring him up on my way in.

55
00:04:47,013 --> 00:04:49,212
They haven't caught the thief yet.

56
00:04:49,212 --> 00:04:51,238
I don't like

57
00:04:51,238 --> 00:04:52,993
leaving you alone.

58
00:04:52,993 --> 00:04:55,126
I'm really okay.

59
00:04:55,126 --> 00:04:58,175
It's late. You should go.

60
00:05:00,297 --> 00:05:03,790
Call me if anything happens.

61
00:05:04,525 --> 00:05:06,383
I will.

62
00:05:08,805 --> 00:05:11,477
Woo Jin...

63
00:05:11,477 --> 00:05:13,445
God...

64
00:05:14,218 --> 00:05:17,250
It's all my fault. All of it.

65
00:05:17,250 --> 00:05:20,306
Because of money...

66
00:05:20,306 --> 00:05:22,526
My fault.

67
00:05:22,526 --> 00:05:25,539
I left you kids behind...

68
00:05:35,895 --> 00:05:38,942
It's been a long time.

69
00:05:42,692 --> 00:05:45,035
Have you been doing okay?

70
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:49,400
You must have resented me a lot.

71
00:05:54,890 --> 00:05:57,024
I don't know.

72
00:05:59,447 --> 00:06:02,360
I wasn't exactly waiting for you.

73
00:06:03,190 --> 00:06:04,216
Tae Hyung, I...

74
00:06:04,216 --> 00:06:06,282
So,

75
00:06:07,468 --> 00:06:09,836
what do you want?

76
00:06:09,836 --> 00:06:10,875
What?

77
00:06:10,875 --> 00:06:13,922
Like you said, it's been a long time.

78
00:06:14,917 --> 00:06:18,577
You didn't just show up like this
without a reason. Right?

79
00:06:18,577 --> 00:06:21,181
A reason? No.

80
00:06:21,181 --> 00:06:23,360
It's not like that.

81
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:25,197
I just wanted to see how you've been.

82
00:06:25,197 --> 00:06:26,993
That's enough.

83
00:06:26,993 --> 00:06:30,637
It's not like we can pick up where we left off.

84
00:06:30,637 --> 00:06:32,800
If you're done talking,

85
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:35,120
please leave.

86
00:06:37,599 --> 00:06:39,871
Okay.

87
00:06:39,871 --> 00:06:42,771
I understand how you feel, Tae Hyung.

88
00:06:44,198 --> 00:06:46,750
It's late,

89
00:06:47,885 --> 00:06:50,218
so I'll go.

90
00:07:13,988 --> 00:07:16,807
[Episode 7]
What is going on? A break-in?

91
00:07:16,807 --> 00:07:19,378
I already called the police.

92
00:07:19,378 --> 00:07:22,038
Hopefully they catch him soon.

93
00:07:23,230 --> 00:07:25,176
Everything feels so chaotic right now.

94
00:07:25,176 --> 00:07:28,562
My heart's still racing.
You must've been really scared.

95
00:07:28,562 --> 00:07:30,008
Thank you for checking on me.

96
00:07:30,008 --> 00:07:31,693
You should get some rest.

97
00:07:31,693 --> 00:07:34,061
Woo Joo, let's go. Say bye.

98
00:07:34,061 --> 00:07:35,923
Bye. Get some rest.

99
00:07:35,923 --> 00:07:37,383
- You too.
- Okay.

100
00:07:46,578 --> 00:07:48,068
Did you have fun?

101
00:07:54,511 --> 00:07:56,321
Tae Hyung.

102
00:07:56,321 --> 00:07:58,279
You okay?

103
00:07:58,279 --> 00:08:00,039
Of course.

104
00:08:00,039 --> 00:08:01,509
Are you okay?

105
00:08:01,509 --> 00:08:04,200
You must've been shaken up.

106
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:05,627
I'm alright.

107
00:08:05,627 --> 00:08:09,735
If anyone was more shocked, it was you.

108
00:08:09,735 --> 00:08:12,275
Did you finish this?

109
00:08:21,643 --> 00:08:23,154
Come here.

110
00:08:23,154 --> 00:08:25,142
- Sit.
- What?

111
00:08:28,529 --> 00:08:29,654
Let me see your hand.

112
00:08:29,654 --> 00:08:31,152
My hand?

113
00:08:31,152 --> 00:08:32,872
Why?

114
00:08:32,872 --> 00:08:35,745
When did I get hurt?

115
00:08:37,181 --> 00:08:39,370
I must've scraped it when I fell earlier.

116
00:08:39,370 --> 00:08:42,547
Scraped it? You're bleeding.

117
00:08:43,167 --> 00:08:45,124
Come here.

118
00:08:46,376 --> 00:08:48,362
I'm fine.

119
00:08:50,638 --> 00:08:53,872
I'm sorry. This happened because of me.

120
00:09:00,364 --> 00:09:02,316
You must've been scared.

121
00:09:02,316 --> 00:09:05,478
Some stranger just walked in...

122
00:09:07,838 --> 00:09:10,639
Why are you apologizing?

123
00:09:10,639 --> 00:09:13,093
You've got enough on your mind.

124
00:09:13,093 --> 00:09:15,319
Don't worry about me.

125
00:09:16,019 --> 00:09:18,685
It's not that.

126
00:09:18,685 --> 00:09:20,908
I've lived longer without him

127
00:09:20,908 --> 00:09:23,286
than with him.

128
00:09:25,477 --> 00:09:27,558
And honestly,

129
00:09:27,558 --> 00:09:29,251
I barely remember him.

130
00:09:29,251 --> 00:09:31,095
He's practically a stranger.

131
00:09:31,095 --> 00:09:34,395
Come on. He's not just some stranger.

132
00:09:35,736 --> 00:09:37,501
Anyway,

133
00:09:37,501 --> 00:09:39,814
I'm sorry I was late.

134
00:09:40,631 --> 00:09:43,100
I should've gotten here sooner.

135
00:09:47,430 --> 00:09:49,836
Be careful. Don't get hurt.

136
00:09:54,235 --> 00:09:55,854
Oh no. What do we do?

137
00:09:55,854 --> 00:09:57,568
What do we do?

138
00:09:57,568 --> 00:09:59,029
Hey.

139
00:09:59,029 --> 00:10:00,563
- Where's your dad?
- I don't know.

140
00:10:00,563 --> 00:10:03,022
Do you have any idea how much money he took?

141
00:10:03,022 --> 00:10:05,788
- Where did he go?
- I don't know where he is.

142
00:10:05,788 --> 00:10:07,248
Where did he go?

143
00:10:07,248 --> 00:10:08,701
Stop lying. Where is he?

144
00:10:08,701 --> 00:10:09,801
You're hiding him, aren't you?

145
00:10:09,801 --> 00:10:11,008
You're in touch with him, right?

146
00:10:11,008 --> 00:10:13,161
Do you even know how much he stole?

147
00:10:13,161 --> 00:10:16,014
Because of your dad, we're all ruined.

148
00:10:49,816 --> 00:10:50,861
Tae Hyung,

149
00:10:50,861 --> 00:10:52,546
you like orange juice, don't you?

150
00:10:52,546 --> 00:10:55,601
Gosh, the ice melted.

151
00:10:55,601 --> 00:10:58,363
Thanks for reaching out.

152
00:10:58,363 --> 00:11:00,674
We're not exactly in a place to catch up.

153
00:11:00,674 --> 00:11:02,966
So I'll get straight to it.

154
00:11:02,966 --> 00:11:04,931
I don't know what this is about,

155
00:11:04,931 --> 00:11:07,839
but showing up out of nowhere like last time,

156
00:11:08,685 --> 00:11:11,720
I don't want that happening again.

157
00:11:15,248 --> 00:11:17,260
Tae Hyung, I'm still your dad...

158
00:11:17,260 --> 00:11:19,194
"Dad?"

159
00:11:20,002 --> 00:11:22,115
You left a little kid behind because of money.

160
00:11:22,115 --> 00:11:24,435
And now you call yourself that?

161
00:11:24,435 --> 00:11:26,088
What,

162
00:11:26,088 --> 00:11:28,248
do you expect to be treated like a dad?

163
00:11:28,248 --> 00:11:31,111
Isn't that completely shameless?

164
00:11:31,111 --> 00:11:33,037
Do you even know

165
00:11:33,037 --> 00:11:36,124
how I've been living all this time?

166
00:11:39,684 --> 00:11:41,777
So let's just

167
00:11:42,731 --> 00:11:45,724
keep living our own lives.

168
00:11:46,633 --> 00:11:49,846
Don't put us in this situation again.

169
00:11:55,404 --> 00:11:57,129
Tae Hyung.

170
00:11:57,129 --> 00:11:58,734
You're right.

171
00:11:58,734 --> 00:12:02,410
I know I have no right coming back like this.

172
00:12:02,410 --> 00:12:04,264
But could you

173
00:12:04,264 --> 00:12:07,362
give me one chance?

174
00:12:07,362 --> 00:12:09,464
It's late, I know.

175
00:12:09,464 --> 00:12:13,290
But I want to try to be a real father.

176
00:12:14,679 --> 00:12:16,945
No.

177
00:12:16,945 --> 00:12:19,627
You don't have to.

178
00:12:19,627 --> 00:12:23,886
I erased the idea of family
from my life a long time ago.

179
00:12:26,893 --> 00:12:28,845
I'm sorry.

180
00:12:31,712 --> 00:12:33,948
I came back

181
00:12:33,948 --> 00:12:35,847
too late.

182
00:12:40,707 --> 00:12:43,714
I hope we never see each other again.

183
00:13:03,860 --> 00:13:04,886
Sir,

184
00:13:04,886 --> 00:13:07,364
is it true we got picked
as this quarter's key project?

185
00:13:07,364 --> 00:13:10,831
I can't believe the GloMarket project
is BS's core project!

186
00:13:10,831 --> 00:13:12,703
Am I getting promoted this time?

187
00:13:12,703 --> 00:13:14,185
Wait,

188
00:13:14,185 --> 00:13:16,546
what exactly is a BS core project?

189
00:13:16,546 --> 00:13:17,638
Oh, right.

190
00:13:17,638 --> 00:13:20,032
You're still on contract.
You probably don't know.

191
00:13:20,032 --> 00:13:22,550
We have an internal company chat.

192
00:13:22,550 --> 00:13:23,783
Full-timers only.

193
00:13:23,783 --> 00:13:26,312
It blew up this morning.

194
00:13:26,312 --> 00:13:27,995
This must be the first you're hearing of it.

195
00:13:27,995 --> 00:13:29,503
No.

196
00:13:29,503 --> 00:13:31,128
It was just finalized.

197
00:13:31,128 --> 00:13:33,894
That's why the announcement was late.

198
00:13:34,658 --> 00:13:37,238
Let me make this official.

199
00:13:37,238 --> 00:13:39,710
Every quarter, headquarters selects

200
00:13:39,710 --> 00:13:41,128
a core strategic project.

201
00:13:41,128 --> 00:13:43,332
And our GloMarket proposal has been chosen.

202
00:13:43,332 --> 00:13:44,967
Yes!

203
00:13:44,967 --> 00:13:46,842
If we pull this off,

204
00:13:46,842 --> 00:13:48,761
the incentives are solid.

205
00:13:48,761 --> 00:13:51,113
And it's a huge boost for performance reviews.

206
00:13:51,113 --> 00:13:52,264
In short,

207
00:13:52,264 --> 00:13:54,817
this is our big shot.

208
00:13:56,561 --> 00:13:57,812
What's wrong, Woo Joo?

209
00:13:57,812 --> 00:13:59,443
Daycare's fun. Right?

210
00:13:59,443 --> 00:14:00,669
Oh no.

211
00:14:00,669 --> 00:14:03,716
He doesn't want to go today?

212
00:14:05,399 --> 00:14:06,823
Why doesn't he want to go?

213
00:14:06,823 --> 00:14:09,201
Once he's there, he's fine.

214
00:14:09,201 --> 00:14:10,700
He just gets like this sometimes.

215
00:14:10,700 --> 00:14:13,359
- Oh dear.
- Give him here.

216
00:14:13,359 --> 00:14:16,163
I'll take him.

217
00:14:16,163 --> 00:14:17,530
You will?

218
00:14:17,530 --> 00:14:20,187
My mom's great with kids
around the neighborhood.

219
00:14:20,187 --> 00:14:23,045
Just think of it as a drop-off helper.

220
00:14:23,045 --> 00:14:26,156
I'd really appreciate it,
I just feel bad imposing.

221
00:14:26,156 --> 00:14:30,177
If you feel that way, then hire her officially.

222
00:14:30,177 --> 00:14:32,013
I'll give you a family discount.

223
00:14:33,106 --> 00:14:34,140
That's nonsense.

224
00:14:34,140 --> 00:14:36,559
- Go on, hurry.
- She would like it.

225
00:14:38,595 --> 00:14:40,354
Then please, grandma.

226
00:14:40,354 --> 00:14:41,547
Okay, don't worry.

227
00:14:41,547 --> 00:14:43,881
Woo Joo, listen to Grandma and be good.

228
00:14:45,241 --> 00:14:47,419
You listen to Grandma too.

229
00:14:47,419 --> 00:14:48,960
I always do.

230
00:14:48,960 --> 00:14:51,599
Bye, see you later.

231
00:14:52,230 --> 00:14:55,210
Say "bye, uncle."

232
00:14:56,614 --> 00:14:59,366
Mom, he's starting to look like a real uncle.

233
00:14:59,366 --> 00:15:03,076
I was worried how a young guy
would raise a kid,

234
00:15:03,076 --> 00:15:06,490
but he's doing pretty well.

235
00:15:06,490 --> 00:15:07,603
Let's go.

236
00:15:07,603 --> 00:15:08,842
Deep bow.

237
00:15:08,842 --> 00:15:10,384
Thank you. One more time.

238
00:15:10,384 --> 00:15:12,326
That's right.

239
00:15:12,326 --> 00:15:14,866
Goodbye.

240
00:15:14,866 --> 00:15:17,828
Woo Joo, did you have fun today?

241
00:15:25,077 --> 00:15:27,090
Hi, Woo Joo.

242
00:15:37,694 --> 00:15:40,793
Thanks for giving us a ride.

243
00:15:40,793 --> 00:15:42,527
Of course I would.

244
00:15:42,527 --> 00:15:46,420
You've been buried in work
with that workaholic boss.

245
00:15:46,420 --> 00:15:48,474
Right?

246
00:15:48,474 --> 00:15:49,678
Yeah,

247
00:15:49,678 --> 00:15:51,911
that's true.

248
00:15:51,911 --> 00:15:52,964
By the way,

249
00:15:52,964 --> 00:15:55,873
do you always pick him up after work?

250
00:15:55,873 --> 00:15:56,913
That must be exhausting.

251
00:15:56,913 --> 00:15:59,920
I try to, whenever I can.

252
00:15:59,920 --> 00:16:02,472
I feel like I don't get enough time with him.

253
00:16:02,472 --> 00:16:04,278
So at least on the walk home,

254
00:16:04,278 --> 00:16:06,698
we get to talk.

255
00:16:07,551 --> 00:16:10,728
You're doing great, Woo Hyun Jin.

256
00:16:10,728 --> 00:16:12,624
That's impressive.

257
00:16:27,147 --> 00:16:29,539
Thank you.

258
00:16:29,539 --> 00:16:31,696
Can I come up for a second?

259
00:16:31,696 --> 00:16:32,864
What?

260
00:16:32,864 --> 00:16:34,737
No.

261
00:16:37,743 --> 00:16:38,840
Oh, I get it.

262
00:16:38,840 --> 00:16:41,999
You're just changing the door lock.

263
00:16:41,999 --> 00:16:44,272
Then why do you think I came up to your place?

264
00:16:44,272 --> 00:16:46,003
No, I mean...

265
00:16:46,003 --> 00:16:49,400
I really wasn't thinking anything weird.

266
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:51,983
Do you have a drill?

267
00:16:51,983 --> 00:16:54,097
This thing's not working.

268
00:16:54,097 --> 00:16:56,763
Yes, I do. One second.

269
00:17:34,170 --> 00:17:36,847
I'm home. Why's the door...

270
00:17:38,967 --> 00:17:41,100
Oh, you're back.

271
00:17:46,703 --> 00:17:48,597
What is this?

272
00:17:50,368 --> 00:17:53,069
What are you doing here this late?

273
00:17:54,698 --> 00:17:56,558
He's replacing the door lock.

274
00:17:56,558 --> 00:17:58,563
You know, he's the landlord.

275
00:17:58,563 --> 00:18:01,119
I'm switching it to a security lock.

276
00:18:01,119 --> 00:18:03,284
Just to be safe.

277
00:18:21,590 --> 00:18:24,061
You've got to hold it steady for it to fit.

278
00:18:24,061 --> 00:18:25,092
It's crooked.

279
00:18:25,092 --> 00:18:26,288
Let go for a second.

280
00:18:26,288 --> 00:18:27,373
Don't force it.

281
00:18:27,373 --> 00:18:28,531
It's sticking out.

282
00:18:28,531 --> 00:18:30,155
See? It's crooked.

283
00:18:30,155 --> 00:18:32,586
- Fix it.
- It's because you just drove it in.

284
00:18:32,586 --> 00:18:33,806
What, then you want me to say

285
00:18:33,806 --> 00:18:36,779
"Here it comes" before I do it?

286
00:18:40,859 --> 00:18:42,722
Hey, kid. It's crooked, right?

287
00:18:44,001 --> 00:18:47,427
See? Kids don't lie.

288
00:18:49,354 --> 00:18:51,348
Come here. It's not safe.

289
00:18:51,348 --> 00:18:52,934
Hyun Jin.

290
00:18:52,934 --> 00:18:54,566
- Yes?
- Where'd she go?

291
00:18:54,566 --> 00:18:55,692
Come here.

292
00:18:55,692 --> 00:18:58,713
- Sleepy?
- Come on.

293
00:18:58,713 --> 00:19:00,322
Got something on you?

294
00:19:00,322 --> 00:19:03,757
What did you get into, Sun Woo Joo?

295
00:19:03,757 --> 00:19:04,874
Woo Joo.

296
00:19:04,874 --> 00:19:06,912
Here.

297
00:19:06,912 --> 00:19:08,878
Hold still.

298
00:19:11,312 --> 00:19:13,634
Drive safe.

299
00:19:13,634 --> 00:19:16,675
If anything happens to Hyun Jin,

300
00:19:16,675 --> 00:19:18,895
please let me know.

301
00:19:20,136 --> 00:19:22,747
There's been a lot going on
in this building lately.

302
00:19:22,747 --> 00:19:24,924
I'm worried.

303
00:19:26,507 --> 00:19:29,412
That's not really your concern.

304
00:19:29,412 --> 00:19:31,519
I'll handle the worrying.

305
00:19:31,519 --> 00:19:33,839
Stay out of my family's business.

306
00:19:33,839 --> 00:19:37,220
I won't let Hyun Jin get hurt.

307
00:19:37,220 --> 00:19:39,549
I'm confident about that.

308
00:19:39,549 --> 00:19:41,436
And you?

309
00:19:41,436 --> 00:19:43,389
Are you confident?

310
00:19:43,389 --> 00:19:44,450
What?

311
00:19:44,450 --> 00:19:46,387
Your father.

312
00:19:46,387 --> 00:19:48,620
He worries me.

313
00:19:48,620 --> 00:19:52,788
It sounded like you haven't been in touch.

314
00:19:52,788 --> 00:19:54,734
And I still can't understand

315
00:19:54,734 --> 00:19:58,754
why he was inside an empty house.

316
00:20:02,001 --> 00:20:04,157
At the very least, while you're living here,

317
00:20:04,157 --> 00:20:07,764
make sure Hyun Jin isn't put at risk

318
00:20:07,764 --> 00:20:09,971
because of you.

319
00:20:30,810 --> 00:20:32,061
Seriously?

320
00:20:32,061 --> 00:20:33,729
I'm honored.

321
00:20:33,729 --> 00:20:34,730
When do I start?

322
00:20:35,815 --> 00:20:38,734
I can't believe I get to work under Amy Choo.

323
00:20:38,734 --> 00:20:41,195
You'll mostly be working with me anyway.

324
00:20:41,195 --> 00:20:42,710
- You sure you're good with that?
- I...

325
00:20:42,710 --> 00:20:46,534
I can't miss the historic moment
you take the lead.

326
00:20:46,534 --> 00:20:50,862
And I get "Filmpluto" on my résumé.

327
00:20:52,116 --> 00:20:53,499
I've got to tell my mom.

328
00:20:53,499 --> 00:20:55,652
I'm calling home.

329
00:21:01,549 --> 00:21:03,229
Something's up with you.

330
00:21:04,635 --> 00:21:07,429
You finally landed the lead.

331
00:21:07,429 --> 00:21:09,415
You should be celebrating.

332
00:21:09,415 --> 00:21:12,475
Instead you look like you need a drink.

333
00:21:13,227 --> 00:21:15,196
What is it?

334
00:21:15,855 --> 00:21:18,228
You've got sharp instincts.

335
00:21:19,792 --> 00:21:21,715
Actually...

336
00:21:22,688 --> 00:21:26,250
A guy claiming to be my father
showed up not long ago.

337
00:21:27,491 --> 00:21:29,440
Your father?

338
00:21:30,119 --> 00:21:33,893
I don't think you've ever talked about him.

339
00:21:33,893 --> 00:21:36,800
He was barely ever home.

340
00:21:38,961 --> 00:21:41,422
He knew he had two little kids,

341
00:21:41,422 --> 00:21:44,808
but he'd mess up and
disappear whenever he could.

342
00:21:46,218 --> 00:21:49,358
He walked away back then,
and now he shows up again.

343
00:21:50,514 --> 00:21:53,107
That's how it always felt.

344
00:21:54,685 --> 00:21:57,479
Even when I was home,

345
00:21:57,479 --> 00:22:00,865
it felt like my heart was somewhere else.

346
00:22:04,153 --> 00:22:06,287
You wouldn't get it.

347
00:22:08,070 --> 00:22:09,856
So what about now?

348
00:22:09,856 --> 00:22:11,148
Now?

349
00:22:11,148 --> 00:22:13,996
In the house you live in now,

350
00:22:13,996 --> 00:22:16,957
do you still feel that way?

351
00:22:16,957 --> 00:22:19,259
Now...

352
00:22:21,795 --> 00:22:24,289
No.

353
00:22:24,289 --> 00:22:26,762
That place actually feels like home.

354
00:22:28,344 --> 00:22:31,864
Sometimes it even feels like a real family.

355
00:22:35,197 --> 00:22:37,959
That's why I'm more afraid.

356
00:22:39,892 --> 00:22:42,925
I'm scared I might ruin it.

357
00:22:45,562 --> 00:22:46,635
Oh gosh.

358
00:22:46,635 --> 00:22:48,197
He should've thrown this out sooner.

359
00:22:48,197 --> 00:22:50,862
Doo Sik's never around when we need him.

360
00:22:50,862 --> 00:22:52,228
- Oh, wait.
- Let's just get rid of it.

361
00:22:52,228 --> 00:22:53,911
Put it down.

362
00:22:53,911 --> 00:22:55,204
It's too heavy. Right?

363
00:22:55,204 --> 00:22:56,330
I've got this.

364
00:22:56,330 --> 00:22:58,732
Goodness.

365
00:22:58,732 --> 00:23:01,835
Oh, thank you.

366
00:23:01,835 --> 00:23:04,046
I don't think I've seen him before.

367
00:23:04,046 --> 00:23:05,312
- Who's he?
- Well...

368
00:23:05,312 --> 00:23:10,025
He's... Woo Joo's uncle's father.

369
00:23:12,680 --> 00:23:13,766
Hello.

370
00:23:13,766 --> 00:23:15,166
Thank you so much.

371
00:23:15,166 --> 00:23:16,767
- Hello.
- Yeah.

372
00:23:16,767 --> 00:23:17,810
Earlier today,

373
00:23:17,810 --> 00:23:21,340
a car came flying out of nowhere
and almost hit the kids.

374
00:23:21,340 --> 00:23:23,065
He saved them.

375
00:23:23,065 --> 00:23:25,544
I'm really grateful.

376
00:23:25,544 --> 00:23:28,288
But why are you still here?

377
00:23:28,288 --> 00:23:30,906
Is no one home?

378
00:23:30,906 --> 00:23:33,139
It's... complicated.

379
00:23:34,660 --> 00:23:35,911
I guess

380
00:23:35,911 --> 00:23:38,183
Tae Hyung doesn't want to see me.

381
00:23:38,183 --> 00:23:39,415
What?

382
00:23:39,415 --> 00:23:44,128
Why would a son not want to see his father?

383
00:23:44,128 --> 00:23:47,172
I was too busy chasing money.

384
00:23:47,172 --> 00:23:50,245
I wasn't much of a dad.

385
00:23:51,373 --> 00:23:53,762
I don't really deserve to be one.

386
00:23:53,762 --> 00:23:56,265
I understand how he feels.

387
00:23:56,265 --> 00:23:58,017
I'll just be satisfied

388
00:23:58,017 --> 00:24:00,652
seeing him from a distance.

389
00:24:00,652 --> 00:24:03,800
What do you mean deserve?

390
00:24:03,800 --> 00:24:07,901
When you can see your child,
you should see them as much as you can.

391
00:24:07,901 --> 00:24:11,613
How is he going to live with that regret later?

392
00:24:11,613 --> 00:24:14,694
Oh, there's Woo Joo's aunt.

393
00:24:14,694 --> 00:24:16,531
Woo Joo!

394
00:24:18,379 --> 00:24:20,180
So cute.

395
00:24:25,919 --> 00:24:27,379
Well...

396
00:24:27,379 --> 00:24:30,507
I'm sorry again about the other day.

397
00:24:30,507 --> 00:24:32,185
I really startled you, didn't I?

398
00:24:32,185 --> 00:24:34,445
Oh, it's okay.

399
00:24:35,095 --> 00:24:37,431
And please, you can speak casually.

400
00:24:37,431 --> 00:24:42,689
I'm not great at that with someone I just met.

401
00:24:42,689 --> 00:24:45,105
If you'd prefer, I'll speak more casually.

402
00:24:45,105 --> 00:24:46,106
By the way,

403
00:24:46,106 --> 00:24:48,067
what's this little guy's name?

404
00:24:48,067 --> 00:24:50,069
Woo Joo. Sun Woo Joo.

405
00:24:50,069 --> 00:24:51,871
Woo Joo.

406
00:24:53,354 --> 00:24:57,143
Would it be okay if I held him?

407
00:25:01,455 --> 00:25:02,993
Sure.

408
00:25:02,993 --> 00:25:05,174
Want this?

409
00:25:08,645 --> 00:25:09,880
Woo Joo. Come here.

410
00:25:09,880 --> 00:25:11,322
There you go.

411
00:25:11,322 --> 00:25:12,549
Good boy.

412
00:25:12,549 --> 00:25:13,926
Hey.

413
00:25:13,926 --> 00:25:15,375
Woo Joo,

414
00:25:15,375 --> 00:25:17,611
do you know who I am?

415
00:25:17,611 --> 00:25:20,146
- No.
- He says no.

416
00:25:21,070 --> 00:25:24,058
He's a handsome boy.

417
00:25:24,058 --> 00:25:26,814
He looks just like Woo Jin when he was little.

418
00:25:26,814 --> 00:25:28,357
Right?

419
00:25:28,357 --> 00:25:30,317
He really does look like Woo Jin.

420
00:25:30,317 --> 00:25:32,729
Especially that nose.

421
00:25:32,729 --> 00:25:36,671
It's just like Woo Jin's when he was a kid.

422
00:25:40,035 --> 00:25:41,453
Actually,

423
00:25:41,453 --> 00:25:44,255
Tae Hyung told me last time

424
00:25:46,667 --> 00:25:50,053
he hoped we'd never see each other again.

425
00:25:51,946 --> 00:25:54,508
He said that?

426
00:25:54,508 --> 00:25:56,468
You know,

427
00:25:56,468 --> 00:25:59,734
you can't just cut off
a parent-child bond like that.

428
00:26:00,389 --> 00:26:02,599
Once I see his face,

429
00:26:02,599 --> 00:26:05,070
I want to see them again.

430
00:26:06,228 --> 00:26:08,469
I want to make up

431
00:26:08,469 --> 00:26:10,812
for everything I did wrong.

432
00:26:11,650 --> 00:26:13,660
That's just how I feel.

433
00:26:15,070 --> 00:26:17,156
So even knowing he doesn't want to see me,

434
00:26:17,156 --> 00:26:19,542
I keep coming back.

435
00:26:20,742 --> 00:26:22,895
I don't know.

436
00:26:27,749 --> 00:26:32,379
I don't know the whole story,

437
00:26:32,379 --> 00:26:35,924
but Tae Hyung will probably need time.

438
00:26:35,924 --> 00:26:41,069
Walls like that don't come down easily.

439
00:26:45,184 --> 00:26:48,152
You're right.

440
00:26:48,896 --> 00:26:52,490
This is all my fault anyway.

441
00:26:54,232 --> 00:27:02,326
If you ever need help, even just a little,
please tell me.

442
00:27:02,326 --> 00:27:05,946
It's not easy raising a child
when you're young.

443
00:27:07,831 --> 00:27:09,737
Okay.

444
00:27:10,667 --> 00:27:11,766
Hey, Woo Joo.

445
00:27:11,766 --> 00:27:13,747
What's that?

446
00:27:13,747 --> 00:27:15,255
A police car?

447
00:27:15,255 --> 00:27:17,943
That's cool.

448
00:27:17,943 --> 00:27:19,736
Does it fly too?

449
00:27:21,178 --> 00:27:22,304
You closed the door.

450
00:27:22,304 --> 00:27:23,804
Ready for takeoff.

451
00:27:23,804 --> 00:27:26,090
Here you go.

452
00:27:26,934 --> 00:27:28,185
Is this for me?

453
00:27:28,185 --> 00:27:30,000
You have it.

454
00:27:31,063 --> 00:27:32,731
Alright, shoes off.

455
00:27:32,731 --> 00:27:34,191
All done. Let's get in.

456
00:27:34,191 --> 00:27:38,257
Mr. Sun Woo Joo, home from work?

457
00:27:39,556 --> 00:27:41,626
You're late.

458
00:27:48,744 --> 00:27:50,597
What?

459
00:27:51,416 --> 00:27:53,210
Actually...

460
00:27:53,210 --> 00:27:56,504
I met your father.

461
00:27:56,504 --> 00:27:57,572
What?

462
00:27:57,572 --> 00:28:01,468
It just happened. We ran into each other.

463
00:28:01,468 --> 00:28:04,233
Did he say anything to you?
Did he ask for money?

464
00:28:04,233 --> 00:28:05,389
No, nothing like that.

465
00:28:05,389 --> 00:28:07,924
He didn't say much.

466
00:28:08,805 --> 00:28:10,185
He just seemed

467
00:28:10,185 --> 00:28:13,480
really happy to see Woo Joo.

468
00:28:13,480 --> 00:28:15,042
He told me

469
00:28:15,042 --> 00:28:18,609
you don't want to see him again.

470
00:28:19,695 --> 00:28:23,288
But he came anyway.
He said he just wanted to see you.

471
00:28:23,288 --> 00:28:26,451
So... you let him see Woo Joo?

472
00:28:26,451 --> 00:28:29,830
You know I cut him off. Why even listen to him?

473
00:28:29,830 --> 00:28:31,984
Do you have any idea how...

474
00:28:33,917 --> 00:28:35,043
Well...

475
00:28:35,043 --> 00:28:37,101
He just wanted to talk.

476
00:28:37,101 --> 00:28:38,839
How was I supposed to refuse?

477
00:28:38,839 --> 00:28:40,173
And whatever happened,

478
00:28:40,173 --> 00:28:42,301
he's still your father.

479
00:28:42,301 --> 00:28:45,377
You could at least hear him out once.

480
00:28:45,377 --> 00:28:47,472
Hear what?

481
00:28:47,472 --> 00:28:49,725
Why he never looked for me
for almost twenty years?

482
00:28:49,725 --> 00:28:51,685
Is that the story?

483
00:28:51,685 --> 00:28:55,721
Leaving a nine-year-old at a children's home
and never coming back.

484
00:28:56,898 --> 00:28:58,651
Sun Woo Jin or him, it's the same thing.

485
00:28:58,651 --> 00:29:01,653
What explanation could there be?

486
00:29:01,653 --> 00:29:03,751
Maybe...

487
00:29:04,615 --> 00:29:07,695
maybe Woo Jin had a reason.

488
00:29:08,535 --> 00:29:10,575
Right.

489
00:29:12,039 --> 00:29:14,499
Then I guess I had a reason to be abandoned.

490
00:29:14,499 --> 00:29:16,084
That's not what I meant.

491
00:29:16,084 --> 00:29:19,504
I've thought about it over and over.

492
00:29:19,504 --> 00:29:21,048
What did I do wrong?

493
00:29:21,048 --> 00:29:23,537
What made my brother, my dad

494
00:29:24,348 --> 00:29:26,927
throw me away?

495
00:29:27,846 --> 00:29:30,499
I've thought about it for years.

496
00:29:31,767 --> 00:29:34,487
And I still don't know.

497
00:29:38,435 --> 00:29:40,428
Honestly...

498
00:29:42,361 --> 00:29:45,601
When Sun Woo Jin said he'd come back for me...

499
00:29:47,824 --> 00:29:50,017
I already knew.

500
00:29:52,120 --> 00:29:54,090
Like,

501
00:29:54,975 --> 00:29:57,561
"He's never coming back."

502
00:29:58,835 --> 00:30:01,276
"So this is how I get left behind."

503
00:30:02,589 --> 00:30:05,467
That's why I forced myself to believe

504
00:30:05,467 --> 00:30:08,482
if I waited, he would come.

505
00:30:10,103 --> 00:30:13,822
If I didn't believe that,
I think I would've lost it.

506
00:30:17,024 --> 00:30:18,980
Tae Hyung...

507
00:30:18,980 --> 00:30:21,775
I didn't mean it like that.

508
00:30:21,775 --> 00:30:24,455
I didn't understand the whole situation.

509
00:30:30,784 --> 00:30:34,037
Talking about this stuff just feels pathetic.

510
00:30:34,955 --> 00:30:37,557
That's why I never did.

511
00:30:40,460 --> 00:30:42,655
At least you...

512
00:30:43,463 --> 00:30:46,092
I thought you'd be on my side.

513
00:31:02,170 --> 00:31:05,944
Gosh, isn't Hanbi Foods shady?

514
00:31:05,944 --> 00:31:07,808
No ethics at all.

515
00:31:07,808 --> 00:31:09,293
[Final Partner Selection On Hold:
Hanbi Food submitted a similar proposal.]

516
00:31:09,293 --> 00:31:11,491
Hanbi Foods beat us to it.

517
00:31:11,491 --> 00:31:13,910
Their proposal is almost identical to ours.

518
00:31:13,910 --> 00:31:16,820
Same menu lineup. Even the same vendors.

519
00:31:16,820 --> 00:31:18,540
So what do we do?

520
00:31:18,540 --> 00:31:21,126
Our vendors are already asking what's going on.

521
00:31:21,126 --> 00:31:24,025
For now, let's each handle what we can.

522
00:31:24,737 --> 00:31:26,625
Hello.

523
00:31:34,097 --> 00:31:35,874
Did you hear about Planning Team 3?

524
00:31:35,874 --> 00:31:38,643
Their whole proposal got leaked.

525
00:31:38,643 --> 00:31:42,230
Hanbi Foods is shady, sure, but who did it?

526
00:31:42,230 --> 00:31:44,222
Who leaked the files to them?

527
00:31:44,222 --> 00:31:45,373
Haven't you heard?

528
00:31:45,373 --> 00:31:47,332
Apparently it was someone
on contract in that team.

529
00:31:47,332 --> 00:31:49,362
Honestly, it was kind of suspicious.

530
00:31:49,362 --> 00:31:51,279
With those credentials, how did she get into BS

531
00:31:51,279 --> 00:31:53,928
and lead a core project as a contract employee?

532
00:31:53,928 --> 00:31:57,370
And Manager Park was always protecting her.

533
00:31:57,370 --> 00:31:58,622
That's true.

534
00:31:58,622 --> 00:32:02,000
Didn't she get in here because of him?

535
00:32:02,000 --> 00:32:05,213
- They went to the same school.
- Right.

536
00:32:07,923 --> 00:32:09,591
It wasn't me.

537
00:32:09,591 --> 00:32:12,260
I didn't leak the proposal.

538
00:32:12,260 --> 00:32:13,512
And like you said,

539
00:32:13,512 --> 00:32:15,247
how would a contract employee

540
00:32:15,247 --> 00:32:18,299
even pull something like that?

541
00:32:18,299 --> 00:32:20,644
Isn't that exactly why you could?

542
00:32:20,644 --> 00:32:21,784
You're on contract.

543
00:32:21,784 --> 00:32:24,523
You probably don't feel
any loyalty to the company.

544
00:32:24,523 --> 00:32:27,234
And in a few months, you'll be gone anyway.

545
00:32:27,234 --> 00:32:30,420
Do you have any proof that I did it?

546
00:32:30,420 --> 00:32:31,738
Well, by that logic,

547
00:32:31,738 --> 00:32:34,366
you don't have proof that you didn't.

548
00:32:34,366 --> 00:32:36,743
You eavesdrop on us and then act like this?

549
00:32:36,743 --> 00:32:38,696
Let's go.

550
00:32:44,290 --> 00:32:48,554
This is the full-timer chat,
and things are getting weird.

551
00:32:48,554 --> 00:32:50,457
[BS Food Internal Chat]
Please manage your files more carefully.

552
00:32:50,457 --> 00:32:53,009
I heard Hanbi Food even tried to recruit her.

553
00:32:53,009 --> 00:32:55,895
Then that proves she leaked it.

554
00:33:04,688 --> 00:33:07,315
I had a feeling you might be out here.

555
00:33:07,315 --> 00:33:09,621
And you are.

556
00:33:13,196 --> 00:33:16,582
I just needed some air.

557
00:33:28,336 --> 00:33:31,214
Don't let the gossip get to you.

558
00:33:31,214 --> 00:33:33,383
This is our project.

559
00:33:33,383 --> 00:33:36,469
And you're doing more than fine.

560
00:33:39,639 --> 00:33:41,933
I'm really okay.

561
00:33:41,933 --> 00:33:44,597
You don't have to pretend in front of me.

562
00:33:44,597 --> 00:33:48,890
If it's hard, just say it's hard.

563
00:33:50,483 --> 00:33:53,528
And sometimes,

564
00:33:53,528 --> 00:33:56,823
lean on me a little.

565
00:33:56,823 --> 00:33:59,951
I want to be someone you can rely on.

566
00:33:59,951 --> 00:34:01,843
Okay?

567
00:34:04,789 --> 00:34:06,842
Okay, I will.

568
00:34:07,459 --> 00:34:09,958
Thank you. Always.

569
00:34:18,002 --> 00:34:22,648
Which one looks more like it was crafted
by a true artisan?

570
00:34:24,935 --> 00:34:26,770
Definitely the one on the right.

571
00:34:26,770 --> 00:34:30,028
It feels more handcrafted.

572
00:34:31,274 --> 00:34:32,317
Good.

573
00:34:32,317 --> 00:34:36,043
Then we'll remove
all leaked concepts from the lineup.

574
00:34:36,043 --> 00:34:39,360
We'll focus on one item, tteokbokki,

575
00:34:39,360 --> 00:34:41,542
the dish that best highlights
the flavor of gochujang.

576
00:34:41,542 --> 00:34:44,287
The samples are ready,

577
00:34:44,287 --> 00:34:46,498
so we can start internal tastings right away.

578
00:34:46,498 --> 00:34:49,000
Then let's schedule the tasting
as soon as possible.

579
00:34:49,000 --> 00:34:50,271
Ms. Woo Hyun Jin,

580
00:34:50,271 --> 00:34:52,480
from now on, focus solely
on preparing the pitch.

581
00:34:52,480 --> 00:34:55,340
Yes, I'll get right on it.

582
00:34:55,340 --> 00:34:58,009
I heard the contract employee
from Planning Team 3 did it.

583
00:34:58,009 --> 00:35:00,637
- Really?
- Yeah, it's all over the office.

584
00:35:00,637 --> 00:35:02,514
That's bold for a temp.

585
00:35:02,514 --> 00:35:05,016
She can't leak to a competitor. Right?

586
00:35:05,016 --> 00:35:07,227
I can't trust new hires these days.

587
00:35:07,227 --> 00:35:08,307
Exactly.

588
00:35:08,307 --> 00:35:11,553
How's she supposed to survive here after this?

589
00:35:16,528 --> 00:35:18,863
You'll probably have to work late tonight,
right?

590
00:35:19,627 --> 00:35:22,882
As you see, things got messy.

591
00:35:24,536 --> 00:35:26,620
About yesterday...

592
00:35:27,497 --> 00:35:30,500
I was too emotional.

593
00:35:30,500 --> 00:35:32,752
I shouldn't have taken it out on you.

594
00:35:32,752 --> 00:35:34,450
No.

595
00:35:34,450 --> 00:35:38,336
I spoke without really knowing the whole story.

596
00:35:39,009 --> 00:35:41,261
Hyun Jin.

597
00:35:41,261 --> 00:35:43,030
Let's go.

598
00:35:43,030 --> 00:35:45,020
Yes.

599
00:35:46,345 --> 00:35:47,646
You look busy.

600
00:35:47,646 --> 00:35:49,151
Go take care of it.

601
00:35:49,151 --> 00:35:51,405
Yeah, I've got another meeting.

602
00:35:51,405 --> 00:35:53,678
Let's talk later.

603
00:36:04,442 --> 00:36:06,202
How could a proposal leak happen?

604
00:36:06,202 --> 00:36:08,913
We have to win the GloMarket deal.

605
00:36:08,913 --> 00:36:10,790
We can't lose this.

606
00:36:10,790 --> 00:36:12,375
How's the pitch coming along?

607
00:36:12,375 --> 00:36:14,655
You know that's the most important part, right?

608
00:36:14,655 --> 00:36:15,795
Yes.

609
00:36:15,795 --> 00:36:18,099
Ms. Woo Hyun Jin has been preparing it.

610
00:36:18,099 --> 00:36:19,999
Who?

611
00:36:19,999 --> 00:36:22,792
I'm preparing it, sir.

612
00:36:24,612 --> 00:36:26,056
Instead of her...

613
00:36:26,056 --> 00:36:28,260
How about Assistant Manager Choi
from Planning Team 1?

614
00:36:28,260 --> 00:36:30,327
From what I saw last time,
with his overseas background,

615
00:36:30,327 --> 00:36:32,771
his English is solid. Very global.

616
00:36:32,771 --> 00:36:33,796
What about him?

617
00:36:33,796 --> 00:36:37,233
Our Planning Team 3
has been developing this project

618
00:36:37,233 --> 00:36:39,682
since before it was selected
as a BS core project.

619
00:36:39,682 --> 00:36:41,029
So it's only right

620
00:36:41,029 --> 00:36:43,505
that someone from our team handles the pitch.

621
00:36:43,505 --> 00:36:45,784
The presenter represents the company.

622
00:36:45,784 --> 00:36:48,286
We need someone of that caliber up there.

623
00:36:48,286 --> 00:36:50,392
Replace her.

624
00:36:51,206 --> 00:36:52,457
Then...

625
00:36:52,457 --> 00:36:54,918
Please review them yourself and decide.

626
00:36:54,918 --> 00:36:56,461
Review what?

627
00:36:56,461 --> 00:36:58,838
Assistant Manager Choi from Planning Team 1
and Staff Woo Hyun Jin.

628
00:36:58,838 --> 00:37:02,467
Please hear both of their pitches
and make the call.

629
00:37:02,467 --> 00:37:04,552
From the company's standpoint,

630
00:37:04,552 --> 00:37:06,096
it does make sense to send

631
00:37:06,096 --> 00:37:08,918
the most capable person
for a high-stakes presentation.

632
00:37:08,918 --> 00:37:10,725
What do you think, sir?

633
00:37:10,725 --> 00:37:15,502
Internal competition for a pitch slot
isn't uncommon.

634
00:37:15,502 --> 00:37:19,788
It may actually be the fairest approach.

635
00:37:22,695 --> 00:37:24,405
Well...

636
00:37:24,405 --> 00:37:26,533
That's not a bad idea.

637
00:37:26,533 --> 00:37:29,485
Ms. Woo Hyun Jin, what's your position?

638
00:37:30,745 --> 00:37:32,789
I'll do it.

639
00:37:32,789 --> 00:37:35,853
I'll compete fairly.

640
00:37:35,853 --> 00:37:38,378
Then, you're the hero of our villa.

641
00:37:38,378 --> 00:37:40,671
You caught the thief. Right?

642
00:37:40,671 --> 00:37:41,756
No, no.

643
00:37:41,756 --> 00:37:44,033
I didn't catch him.

644
00:37:44,033 --> 00:37:46,469
They just said my testimony helped.

645
00:37:46,469 --> 00:37:48,096
That's basically the same thing.

646
00:37:48,096 --> 00:37:49,964
- Exactly.
- Yeah.

647
00:37:49,964 --> 00:37:51,141
But mister,

648
00:37:51,141 --> 00:37:54,657
have you still not made up
with Woo Joo's uncle?

649
00:37:56,396 --> 00:37:58,356
That guy has no respect.

650
00:37:58,356 --> 00:38:00,108
That brat has no manners.

651
00:38:00,108 --> 00:38:01,734
I could tell the first time I saw him.

652
00:38:01,734 --> 00:38:03,314
He's got zero manners.

653
00:38:03,314 --> 00:38:04,737
Yeah, he was a little rude.

654
00:38:04,737 --> 00:38:06,990
That's what I'm saying.

655
00:38:06,990 --> 00:38:09,200
Don't be too hard on him.

656
00:38:09,200 --> 00:38:12,127
It's because I wasn't much of a father.

657
00:38:12,912 --> 00:38:14,532
Honestly,

658
00:38:14,532 --> 00:38:17,750
just seeing his face in passing

659
00:38:17,750 --> 00:38:19,961
is enough for me.

660
00:38:19,961 --> 00:38:22,630
Oh my, oh my. What's going on?

661
00:38:22,630 --> 00:38:23,673
Unit 301!

662
00:38:23,673 --> 00:38:26,134
I will help you.

663
00:38:26,134 --> 00:38:28,678
Oh gosh, my back.

664
00:38:28,678 --> 00:38:30,138
He's so kind.

665
00:38:30,138 --> 00:38:32,082
Hello.

666
00:38:33,737 --> 00:38:35,700
Thank you.

667
00:38:52,160 --> 00:38:54,100
Tae Hyung.

668
00:39:00,251 --> 00:39:03,017
Oh my, that rude guy.

669
00:39:12,228 --> 00:39:14,662
Oh, it's already this late...

670
00:39:18,478 --> 00:39:20,262
Woo Hyun Jin.

671
00:39:21,594 --> 00:39:22,857
Yoon Seong?

672
00:39:22,857 --> 00:39:24,275
You're still here?

673
00:39:24,275 --> 00:39:25,598
Just about to leave.

674
00:39:25,598 --> 00:39:27,904
Get in.

675
00:39:27,904 --> 00:39:29,968
Thank you.

676
00:39:43,798 --> 00:39:46,172
The number you're calling is not...

677
00:39:46,172 --> 00:39:49,152
Why isn't she picking up?

678
00:39:50,176 --> 00:39:52,220
She's not picking up?

679
00:39:52,220 --> 00:39:54,138
No, she's not.

680
00:39:54,138 --> 00:39:55,464
Your aunt's not picking up.

681
00:39:55,464 --> 00:39:56,641
Try calling her.

682
00:39:56,641 --> 00:39:58,893
Is Auntie not picking up?

683
00:39:58,893 --> 00:40:01,058
No, still not.

684
00:40:08,027 --> 00:40:10,280
Thanks for the ride.

685
00:40:10,280 --> 00:40:12,365
Hyun Jin.

686
00:40:12,365 --> 00:40:15,702
If you ever need my help, just say the word.

687
00:40:15,702 --> 00:40:18,087
I'll back you up.

688
00:40:21,791 --> 00:40:23,726
Yoon Seong.

689
00:40:23,726 --> 00:40:25,670
Can I ask you one favor?

690
00:40:25,670 --> 00:40:27,714
Sure. Anything.

691
00:40:27,714 --> 00:40:30,967
This time, I don't want your help.

692
00:40:30,967 --> 00:40:31,968
What?

693
00:40:31,968 --> 00:40:34,137
I want to do this on my own.

694
00:40:34,137 --> 00:40:36,431
Without relying on you.

695
00:40:36,431 --> 00:40:39,309
I need to prove myself with my own skills

696
00:40:39,309 --> 00:40:43,440
so I can stand tall in front of everyone.

697
00:40:43,440 --> 00:40:45,328
Woo Hyun Jin...

698
00:40:49,490 --> 00:40:51,630
Alright.

699
00:40:52,655 --> 00:40:55,158
Looks like you've made up your mind.

700
00:40:55,158 --> 00:40:57,285
Thank you for understanding.

701
00:40:57,285 --> 00:40:59,120
It's not about understanding.

702
00:40:59,120 --> 00:41:01,331
It's about believing in you.

703
00:41:01,331 --> 00:41:05,376
I know you can handle this on your own.

704
00:41:05,376 --> 00:41:07,795
Just remember one thing.

705
00:41:07,795 --> 00:41:10,404
I'll always be behind you.

706
00:41:10,404 --> 00:41:12,967
Whether it's help or just someone to lean on,

707
00:41:12,967 --> 00:41:15,393
come to me if you need it.

708
00:41:24,437 --> 00:41:26,134
Woo Joo?

709
00:41:26,134 --> 00:41:28,053
Why are you here...

710
00:41:28,053 --> 00:41:30,193
You said you were leaving
but didn't answer your phone.

711
00:41:30,193 --> 00:41:31,861
We were worried.

712
00:41:31,861 --> 00:41:33,905
- Sorry.
- Auntie.

713
00:41:34,947 --> 00:41:37,986
Yoon Seong, I should go.

714
00:41:42,419 --> 00:41:43,481
Yoon Seong,

715
00:41:43,481 --> 00:41:46,064
It's late. You should head home too.

716
00:41:46,709 --> 00:41:48,628
Thank you.

717
00:41:48,628 --> 00:41:50,329
For what?

718
00:41:50,329 --> 00:41:51,964
For...

719
00:41:51,964 --> 00:41:55,426
not letting her go home alone this late.

720
00:41:55,426 --> 00:41:59,392
That's not something you need to thank me for.

721
00:42:03,476 --> 00:42:05,269
Woo Joo, your auntie's late, huh?

722
00:42:05,269 --> 00:42:07,242
Hyun Jin.

723
00:42:08,272 --> 00:42:10,951
I'll trust you and wait.

724
00:42:10,951 --> 00:42:13,807
When this project is over,

725
00:42:13,807 --> 00:42:16,160
let's go on a date.

726
00:42:29,360 --> 00:42:31,249
Hyun Jin.

727
00:42:32,609 --> 00:42:34,231
Do you still...

728
00:42:34,231 --> 00:42:36,956
have feelings for Manager Park?

729
00:42:36,956 --> 00:42:38,838
What?

730
00:42:40,125 --> 00:42:41,163
Well...

731
00:42:41,163 --> 00:42:44,245
Why would you ask that all of a sudden?

732
00:42:44,245 --> 00:42:45,313
I was just...

733
00:42:45,313 --> 00:42:49,212
curious how you really feel about him.

734
00:42:50,604 --> 00:42:53,317
And I wondered if you'd forgotten how I feel.

735
00:42:55,006 --> 00:42:57,524
I just wanted to say

736
00:42:57,524 --> 00:42:59,785
I'm here too, right beside you.

737
00:43:10,355 --> 00:43:12,578
Woo Joo's awake.

738
00:43:25,144 --> 00:43:27,097
I just wanted to say

739
00:43:27,097 --> 00:43:29,419
I'm here too, right beside you.

740
00:43:33,044 --> 00:43:36,424
Why would he say something like that...

741
00:43:37,966 --> 00:43:41,595
It's not like I don't know
he's always been by my side.

742
00:43:41,595 --> 00:43:44,192
When this project is over,

743
00:43:44,192 --> 00:43:46,652
let's go on a date.

744
00:43:47,309 --> 00:43:48,351
Whatever...

745
00:43:48,351 --> 00:43:49,603
Get it together.

746
00:43:49,603 --> 00:43:51,207
Focus on what's urgent.

747
00:43:51,207 --> 00:43:53,207
Work comes first.

748
00:44:54,826 --> 00:44:57,623
When did I fall asleep?

749
00:44:59,421 --> 00:45:00,757
You tired?

750
00:45:00,757 --> 00:45:03,351
Come on. I'll drive you home.

751
00:45:04,169 --> 00:45:07,013
No, I'm wide awake now.

752
00:45:07,013 --> 00:45:09,015
Aren't you heading out?

753
00:45:12,687 --> 00:45:14,587
I should...

754
00:45:14,587 --> 00:45:17,560
but I've got a mountain of work tonight.

755
00:46:09,701 --> 00:46:11,077
Oh, you're up?

756
00:46:11,077 --> 00:46:12,997
Come eat.

757
00:46:17,250 --> 00:46:18,543
Did you sleep well?

758
00:46:20,211 --> 00:46:21,755
When did you make all this?

759
00:46:21,755 --> 00:46:24,713
You haven't been eating properly lately.

760
00:46:24,713 --> 00:46:26,628
Eat.

761
00:46:27,218 --> 00:46:29,570
Thanks for the meal.

762
00:46:34,559 --> 00:46:36,745
This is so good.

763
00:46:42,776 --> 00:46:44,976
Is it good?

764
00:46:48,569 --> 00:46:50,496
Hey...

765
00:46:51,156 --> 00:46:53,174
Is something going on lately?

766
00:46:54,371 --> 00:46:56,206
I told you.

767
00:46:56,206 --> 00:46:59,242
Things are crazy because of that competitor.

768
00:46:59,242 --> 00:47:00,284
Really?

769
00:47:00,284 --> 00:47:02,379
Yeah, it's all over the office.

770
00:47:02,379 --> 00:47:04,964
That's bold for a temp.

771
00:47:04,964 --> 00:47:07,583
I don't think that's all of it.

772
00:47:09,803 --> 00:47:12,963
What is it? What happened?

773
00:47:15,517 --> 00:47:18,730
Well... actually...

774
00:47:18,730 --> 00:47:20,689
What? Are they insane?

775
00:47:20,689 --> 00:47:23,842
Accusing someone without proof
is workplace harassment.

776
00:47:23,842 --> 00:47:24,909
This isn't right.

777
00:47:24,909 --> 00:47:26,486
Call HR.

778
00:47:26,486 --> 00:47:28,527
This needs to be reported.

779
00:47:28,527 --> 00:47:30,615
Come on, it's not that serious.

780
00:47:30,615 --> 00:47:33,526
It is. Treating you differently
because you're a contract worker,

781
00:47:33,526 --> 00:47:35,412
looking down on you, that's harassment.

782
00:47:35,412 --> 00:47:38,540
People like that only learn
when it happens to them.

783
00:47:38,540 --> 00:47:39,646
This makes me so mad.

784
00:47:39,646 --> 00:47:41,102
Right?

785
00:47:42,468 --> 00:47:44,980
Hearing you say that
makes me feel so much better.

786
00:47:44,980 --> 00:47:47,632
That's why I end up telling you everything.

787
00:47:47,632 --> 00:47:49,573
Hey, Hyun Jin.

788
00:47:49,573 --> 00:47:51,946
Why don't you come to our shoot today?

789
00:47:51,946 --> 00:47:53,655
Your shoot?

790
00:47:53,655 --> 00:47:55,306
We're filming a global brand today.

791
00:47:55,306 --> 00:47:56,933
All the models are foreigners.

792
00:47:56,933 --> 00:47:58,601
You said what you need right now

793
00:47:58,601 --> 00:48:00,311
is real market feedback, right?

794
00:48:00,311 --> 00:48:02,230
Instead of staring at data all day,

795
00:48:02,230 --> 00:48:05,150
why not have them taste it

796
00:48:05,150 --> 00:48:07,235
and get real reactions?

797
00:48:07,235 --> 00:48:08,361
Seriously?

798
00:48:08,361 --> 00:48:10,879
That would be amazing.

799
00:48:10,879 --> 00:48:12,807
Yes!

800
00:48:12,807 --> 00:48:14,727
Wait...

801
00:48:15,621 --> 00:48:19,372
Then... what about Woo Joo?

802
00:48:19,372 --> 00:48:21,338
Woo Joo?

803
00:48:24,282 --> 00:48:26,504
It's my mother-in-law's birthday today,

804
00:48:26,504 --> 00:48:28,419
we were just heading out for dinner.

805
00:48:28,419 --> 00:48:31,134
I see. Then it can't be helped.

806
00:48:31,134 --> 00:48:32,510
Hello, Se Yeon.

807
00:48:32,510 --> 00:48:35,722
Can you look after Woo Joo for a little while?

808
00:48:35,722 --> 00:48:38,141
Ui Jun, do you have time?

809
00:48:38,141 --> 00:48:40,047
Okay.

810
00:48:44,898 --> 00:48:47,442
Of all days, everyone's busy today.

811
00:48:47,442 --> 00:48:48,810
What do we do?

812
00:48:48,810 --> 00:48:52,906
We can't take Woo Joo to the shoot.

813
00:48:52,906 --> 00:48:56,250
I guess we don't have a choice.

814
00:49:02,957 --> 00:49:04,070
Hello?

815
00:49:04,070 --> 00:49:06,544
Hey, Unit 206. You called?

816
00:49:06,544 --> 00:49:07,796
Is something wrong?

817
00:49:07,796 --> 00:49:10,340
We need to step out urgently.

818
00:49:10,340 --> 00:49:13,092
Could you take care of Woo Joo for a bit?

819
00:49:14,469 --> 00:49:15,553
Oh dear...

820
00:49:15,553 --> 00:49:17,880
I'm out hiking with my mom right now.

821
00:49:17,880 --> 00:49:19,992
She's asking if we can look after Woo Joo.

822
00:49:21,851 --> 00:49:23,042
Okay.

823
00:49:23,042 --> 00:49:24,145
It can't be helped.

824
00:49:24,145 --> 00:49:26,125
Woo Joo's grandfather could take care of him.

825
00:49:26,125 --> 00:49:28,191
Oh right, then

826
00:49:28,191 --> 00:49:30,568
why don't you ask his grandfather?

827
00:49:30,568 --> 00:49:32,570
He's been saying he really misses Woo Joo.

828
00:49:32,570 --> 00:49:35,100
And Woo Joo absolutely loves him.

829
00:49:35,100 --> 00:49:37,335
Oh no, Never mind.

830
00:49:37,335 --> 00:49:39,219
Enjoy your time.

831
00:49:39,219 --> 00:49:41,126
Okay.

832
00:49:44,397 --> 00:49:47,564
Woo Joo, your Grandpa is here.

833
00:49:48,419 --> 00:49:49,629
Woo Joo, look at this.

834
00:49:49,629 --> 00:49:51,047
See the dinosaur?

835
00:49:51,047 --> 00:49:53,139
With the dinosaur...

836
00:49:54,525 --> 00:49:56,539
His food's in the fridge.

837
00:49:56,539 --> 00:49:58,615
And the diapers are right here.

838
00:49:58,615 --> 00:50:01,099
And if anything happens,

839
00:50:01,099 --> 00:50:02,934
please call me right away.

840
00:50:02,934 --> 00:50:04,672
Alright, don't worry.

841
00:50:04,672 --> 00:50:05,979
You said you're busy. Go on.

842
00:50:05,979 --> 00:50:08,815
Thank you.

843
00:50:08,815 --> 00:50:10,908
It disappeared, didn't it?

844
00:50:11,569 --> 00:50:12,709
Where do you think it is?

845
00:50:12,709 --> 00:50:13,736
Here it is.

846
00:50:13,736 --> 00:50:16,222
You got it right.

847
00:50:20,967 --> 00:50:23,072
The dinosaur is here.

848
00:50:24,974 --> 00:50:27,000
Look at this.

849
00:50:30,420 --> 00:50:33,326
Chan Woo, bring the light in a little.

850
00:51:03,661 --> 00:51:05,580
We'll focus on the natural elements

851
00:51:05,580 --> 00:51:07,457
and shoot a lot using the background.

852
00:51:07,457 --> 00:51:10,243
It's my first time seeing him work like this.

853
00:51:19,093 --> 00:51:21,146
Oh, nice.

854
00:51:47,896 --> 00:51:49,422
- Hi, everyone.
- Hi.

855
00:51:49,422 --> 00:51:50,758
Can I have your attention please?

856
00:51:50,758 --> 00:51:51,823
Oh, sure.

857
00:51:51,823 --> 00:51:54,454
First of all,
thank you so much for helping us today.

858
00:51:54,454 --> 00:51:56,154
I really appreciate it.

859
00:51:56,154 --> 00:51:58,451
Try some tteokbokki and
let me know what you think.

860
00:51:58,451 --> 00:52:00,813
It doesn't matter if it's good or bad.

861
00:52:00,813 --> 00:52:02,909
I want to know your honest opinion.

862
00:52:02,909 --> 00:52:04,589
- Is it free?
- Yes, it's free.

863
00:52:04,589 --> 00:52:06,848
Because I love free food.

864
00:52:06,848 --> 00:52:08,755
I love the free meals!

865
00:52:08,755 --> 00:52:10,001
I can't wait!

866
00:52:13,745 --> 00:52:15,155
- Is this spicy?
- Yes, it's spicy.

867
00:52:15,155 --> 00:52:16,440
Nice.

868
00:52:16,440 --> 00:52:17,731
Let me smell it.

869
00:52:20,521 --> 00:52:22,011
- Thank you.
- What do you have here?

870
00:52:22,011 --> 00:52:23,033
What is this?

871
00:52:24,201 --> 00:52:25,547
Thank you.

872
00:52:29,613 --> 00:52:31,212
It's good.

873
00:52:31,212 --> 00:52:32,410
How is it?

874
00:52:32,410 --> 00:52:34,136
- It's so good.
- Good?

875
00:52:35,576 --> 00:52:36,601
Thanks.

876
00:52:36,601 --> 00:52:37,791
Can I interview you?

877
00:52:37,791 --> 00:52:39,240
- Sure, go ahead.
- Go.

878
00:52:39,240 --> 00:52:40,433
Thank you.

879
00:52:41,513 --> 00:52:43,053
Come on.

880
00:52:43,053 --> 00:52:45,120
- Delicious.
- Oh my god. Okay, we got it.

881
00:52:46,180 --> 00:52:47,220
I don't know.

882
00:52:56,017 --> 00:52:58,901
Today's been insane.

883
00:52:58,901 --> 00:53:00,821
Did you get any good feedback?

884
00:53:00,821 --> 00:53:02,113
Yeah. A lot.

885
00:53:02,113 --> 00:53:04,101
That's a relief.

886
00:53:04,741 --> 00:53:06,284
Oh, it's raining.

887
00:53:06,284 --> 00:53:07,326
It is.

888
00:53:07,326 --> 00:53:09,370
They didn't say anything about rain today.

889
00:53:09,370 --> 00:53:11,462
What do we do?

890
00:53:13,166 --> 00:53:15,095
Woo Hyun Jin.

891
00:53:29,390 --> 00:53:32,018
At least we found somewhere to take cover.

892
00:53:32,018 --> 00:53:33,269
You're not cold, are you?

893
00:53:33,269 --> 00:53:35,229
Why did it get dark so fast?

894
00:53:35,229 --> 00:53:37,315
The moon's out.

895
00:53:40,008 --> 00:53:41,837
Why are you smiling?

896
00:53:41,837 --> 00:53:43,783
Because I'm happy.

897
00:53:44,447 --> 00:53:47,492
I told you I like rainy days.

898
00:53:47,492 --> 00:53:50,508
Even though you said you don't.

899
00:53:51,534 --> 00:53:53,831
Well...

900
00:53:53,831 --> 00:53:57,354
Maybe it's not so bad.

901
00:54:00,963 --> 00:54:03,249
It'll stop soon.

902
00:54:36,322 --> 00:54:37,419
Oh no.

903
00:54:37,419 --> 00:54:40,319
You're completely soaked.

904
00:54:40,319 --> 00:54:41,546
It's fine.

905
00:54:41,546 --> 00:54:44,292
It's just a little rain. That's nothing.

906
00:54:46,310 --> 00:54:48,543
If it's just this much rain,

907
00:54:49,595 --> 00:54:51,859
I don't mind

908
00:54:51,859 --> 00:54:55,048
getting soaked with you.

909
00:54:56,665 --> 00:54:58,521
So...

910
00:54:58,521 --> 00:55:01,914
if things ever get tough, tell me.

911
00:55:03,192 --> 00:55:06,362
I may not be your umbrella,

912
00:55:06,362 --> 00:55:09,795
but at least until the rain falling on you

913
00:55:11,450 --> 00:55:13,585
finally stops,

914
00:55:14,704 --> 00:55:17,183
I can stay by your side.

915
00:55:23,588 --> 00:55:25,514
You too...

916
00:55:27,592 --> 00:55:30,477
You can do the same for me.

917
00:55:31,321 --> 00:55:32,847
I'm

918
00:55:32,847 --> 00:55:35,213
always on your side too.

919
00:55:36,142 --> 00:55:37,852
Back then...

920
00:55:37,852 --> 00:55:39,378
I just said that out of frustration.

921
00:55:39,378 --> 00:55:40,730
Forget it.

922
00:55:40,730 --> 00:55:41,813
I just...

923
00:55:41,813 --> 00:55:43,608
didn't want you to misunderstand.

924
00:55:43,608 --> 00:55:45,926
No misunderstandings, okay?

925
00:55:45,926 --> 00:55:48,519
I'm really on your side.

926
00:55:49,458 --> 00:55:50,632
Sure?

927
00:55:51,782 --> 00:55:53,682
Sure.

928
00:56:03,544 --> 00:56:05,213
I think I like it.

929
00:56:05,213 --> 00:56:07,144
Like what?

930
00:56:11,010 --> 00:56:13,040
Rainy days.

931
00:56:20,036 --> 00:56:22,271
That's good.

932
00:56:22,271 --> 00:56:25,210
Now we have something we both like.

933
00:56:28,527 --> 00:56:30,446
For this tteokbokki meal kit,

934
00:56:30,446 --> 00:56:34,533
we plan to specifically tailor it
to suit global tastes.

935
00:56:34,533 --> 00:56:39,330
We'll introduce a soy-based option
and position it as the main flavor.

936
00:56:39,330 --> 00:56:40,481
Hello.

937
00:56:40,481 --> 00:56:43,079
I'm Woo Hyun Jin from Planning Team 3.

938
00:56:43,079 --> 00:56:44,710
A few years ago,

939
00:56:44,710 --> 00:56:48,210
BS failed to secure the final contract
with GloMarket.

940
00:56:48,210 --> 00:56:50,049
But now, years later,

941
00:56:50,049 --> 00:56:52,677
why is GloMarket so receptive

942
00:56:52,677 --> 00:56:54,136
to our proposal?

943
00:56:54,136 --> 00:56:55,724
The answer lies

944
00:56:55,724 --> 00:56:58,556
in the global rise of K-culture.

945
00:56:58,556 --> 00:57:01,343
"Bringing out the true essence of K-food."

946
00:57:01,343 --> 00:57:04,617
For example, when people think of tteokbokki,

947
00:57:04,617 --> 00:57:06,188
they expect bold heat.

948
00:57:06,188 --> 00:57:09,332
So we plan to highlight
that signature spiciness even more.

949
00:57:14,523 --> 00:57:15,720
[On-site reaction footage]

950
00:57:15,720 --> 00:57:17,246
- This is really good.
- It's good.

951
00:57:18,743 --> 00:57:20,273
Because I'm really good with spicy one.

952
00:57:20,273 --> 00:57:21,583
I'm the king of spicy food.

953
00:57:24,929 --> 00:57:27,154
It's spicy, but it's delicious.

954
00:57:27,154 --> 00:57:28,893
I think this sauce is amazing.

955
00:57:29,682 --> 00:57:31,855
It's hot, but it's so good.

956
00:57:32,591 --> 00:57:35,177
[A Focus on Cultural Experience]
BS's first slogan in challenging GloMarket

957
00:57:35,177 --> 00:57:37,138
was this.

958
00:57:37,138 --> 00:57:40,225
"Not just experiencing food,"

959
00:57:40,225 --> 00:57:42,393
"but experiencing culture."

960
00:57:42,393 --> 00:57:44,061
We should remember this.

961
00:57:44,061 --> 00:57:46,071
What do you think?

962
00:58:01,713 --> 00:58:04,353
This GloMarket pitch

963
00:58:05,041 --> 00:58:07,766
will be handled by our team.

964
00:58:08,502 --> 00:58:09,979
Ms. Woo Hyun Jin,

965
00:58:09,979 --> 00:58:12,094
great work.

966
00:58:15,725 --> 00:58:18,465
[Temporary helper]
Did your presentation go well?

967
00:58:27,521 --> 00:58:29,023
Really?

968
00:58:29,023 --> 00:58:30,063
Really?

969
00:58:30,063 --> 00:58:31,984
Yeah, I knew she'd pull it off.

970
00:58:31,984 --> 00:58:34,737
Woo Joo, your auntie did it.

971
00:58:34,737 --> 00:58:35,802
High five.

972
00:58:35,802 --> 00:58:37,853
High five.

973
00:58:42,483 --> 00:58:44,989
So many cakes, right?

974
00:58:46,810 --> 00:58:48,959
Which one should we get?

975
00:58:48,959 --> 00:58:51,220
Which one do you want? Pick one.

976
00:58:51,220 --> 00:58:53,452
Which one?

977
00:58:53,452 --> 00:58:54,650
That one?

978
00:58:54,650 --> 00:58:55,716
- Yeah.
- Okay.

979
00:58:55,716 --> 00:58:56,879
We'll take this one, please.

980
00:58:56,879 --> 00:58:58,692
Okay.

981
00:58:59,678 --> 00:59:00,738
Woo Joo,

982
00:59:00,738 --> 00:59:02,289
let's throw her a proper celebration.

983
00:59:02,289 --> 00:59:03,360
On three,

984
00:59:03,360 --> 00:59:06,162
we go blow, okay?

985
00:59:15,069 --> 00:59:16,984
What?

986
00:59:17,613 --> 00:59:19,931
I don't have an umbrella...

987
00:59:32,784 --> 00:59:34,802
Yoon Seong?

988
00:59:42,596 --> 00:59:44,682
I like you.

989
00:59:48,833 --> 00:59:51,473
I really like you, Woo Hyun Jin.

990
01:00:51,123 --> 01:00:52,828
What? See, I told you.

991
01:00:52,828 --> 01:00:54,654
I said he had feelings for you.

992
01:00:54,654 --> 01:00:56,454
Just go out with me three times.

993
01:00:56,454 --> 01:00:57,478
As a man.

994
01:00:57,478 --> 01:00:58,778
It worked!

995
01:00:58,778 --> 01:01:00,891
Wait, hold on. Why are you tying your hair?

996
01:01:00,891 --> 01:01:02,094
Want to do it together?

997
01:01:02,094 --> 01:01:03,554
Did you two... sleep together?

998
01:01:03,554 --> 01:01:05,761
Hyun Jin, I knew you could do it.

999
01:01:05,761 --> 01:01:06,785
Hyun Jin!

1000
01:01:06,785 --> 01:01:08,819
- Where are we going?
- Let's go clear your head.

1001
01:01:08,819 --> 01:01:11,218
I'm not just going to stand back anymore.

1002
01:01:11,218 --> 01:01:12,243
Tae Hyung.

1003
01:01:12,243 --> 01:01:14,245
So annoying...

1004
01:01:14,245 --> 01:01:15,462
Woo Joo...

1005
01:01:15,462 --> 01:01:17,236
- Woo Joo!
- Mommy!

1006
01:01:17,236 --> 01:01:19,909
They're from the insurance company.
